    "recap_headline": "University of Alabama at Birmingham Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BIRMINGHAM\n\u2013 UAB Baseball got out front early and never looked back on Sunday afternoon as the Blazers (12-8) took down Belmont (8-12) by a score of 12-2. Despite only tallying nine hits, the Green and Gold made the most of their nine walks drawn on the day.\nUAB recorded its second run-rule victory of the weekend over the Bruins, outscoring BU 25-5 in those two games.\nThe Blazers got the scoring started in the bottom of the first when\nAndrew Hunt\nsingled home\nLandon Beaver\nto give UAB an early 1-0 lead. UAB advances to 9-0 when scoring first and 8-2 when scoring in the first inning.\nThe Green and Gold responded with four more runs in the bottom of the second.\nAlex Dupuy\ndropped a single into center field to bring home\nKevin Hall Jr.\nand\nAustin Pierzynski\n. After an intentional walk,\nLandon Beaver\nwas hit by a pitch which scored\nBaylor Roberts\n.\nAndrew Hunt\nalso walked with the bases loaded to cap off the 4-run inning. All base runners got on base with two outs.\nFour more crossed the plate in the bottom half of the fourth for UAB.\nAndrew Hunt\nreached on a fielder's choice as two runs scored on a Belmont error. Hunt and\nLandon Beaver\nwould come around to score on a\nBrady Waugh\ntriple to put UAB up, 9-0 after four innings.\nBelmont would score its two runs in the top of the fifth inning. Brody Langlotz and Nate Webb both crossed the plate in the inning to cut the UAB lead to 9-2.\nChristian Helmers\nand\nBrendan Conner\nwere stellar in their respective outings combining for one earned run across eight innings of work. The duo struck out five and allowed four hits. Conner was credited with his second win of the season.\nThe Blazers pushed their final three runs across in the bottom of the eighth inning.\nWesley Helms\ngot the scoring started on a sac fly which scored\nLandon Beaver\n.\nBrady Waugh\nscored on another Belmont miscue to bring up\nBaylor Roberts\n. Roberts would bring home\nKevin Hall Jr.\non a single to clinch the 12-2 run-rule victory.\nNOTES\n-\nLandon Beaver\nrecorded his fifth multi-hit game of the season.\n-\nBrady Waugh's\ntwo hits were good for his seventh multi-hit game which ranks second on the team.\n- Waugh (6),\nAndrew Hunt\n(4), and\nAlex Dupuy\n(4) all picked up multi-RBI games. Waugh's six multi-RBI games lead the team.\n- In his first career start,\nChristian Helmers\ntossed a career-high 4.1 innings pitched and surrendered just one run.\n-\nBrendan Conner\npicked up the win as he threw the final 3.2 innings of the game. Conner struck out two and allowed one hit and no runs and recorded his third career win.\n- UAB improves to 8-0 when it outhits its opponents.\nFOLLOW THE BLAZERS\nFor more information on the UAB Baseball team, follow @UAB_Baseball on X and Instagram.\nCompetitive Excellence Fund\nIn the current landscape of college athletics, the Competitive Excellence Fund has become integral in our department's mission to Win Champions, Graduate with Honors, and Impact the community. Through your generosity, our coaches will have the greatest opportunity to recruit, retain, and resource talented student athletes worthy of wearing a UAB uniform.\nClick here\nor connect with Blazer Boosters on how you can continue to fuel success."
